終傅.definition: (Catholicism) extreme unction (the sacrament of Anointing of the Sick)

終南山.definition: Zhongnan Mountains, near Xi'an; also known as the Taiyi Mountains

終南捷徑.definition: lit. the Mount Zhongnan shortcut (idiom); fig. shortcut to a high-flying career; easy route to success (an allusion to the Tang Dynasty story of 盧藏用|卢藏用[Lu2 Cang4 yong4], who lived like a hermit on Mt. Zhongnan in order to gain a reputation for wisdom, which he then used to gain a position in the Imperial Court)

終場.definition: end (of a performance or sports match); last round of testing in the imperial examinations

終場鑼聲.definition: the final bell (esp. in sports competition)

終天.definition: all day long; all one's life

終局.definition: endgame; conclusion; outcome; final part of a chess game

終年.definition: entire year; throughout the year; age at death

終成眷屬.definition: see 有情人終成眷屬|有情人终成眷属[you3 qing2 ren2 zhong1 cheng2 juan4 shu3]

終於.definition: at last; in the end; finally; eventually

終究.definition: in the end; after all is said and done

終結.definition: end; conclusion; to come to an end; to terminate (sth)

終而復始.definition: lit. the end comes back to the start (idiom); the wheel comes full circle

終聲.definition: the final of a Korean syllable (consonant or consonant cluster at the end of the syllable)

終身俸.definition: (Tw) pension (for retired military, civil service and teaching personnel)

終身大事.definition: major turning point of lifelong import (esp. marriage)

終點.definition: the end; end point; finishing line (in a race); destination; terminus; CL:個|个[ge4]

終點站.definition: terminus; final stop on rail or bus line
